  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Assistance en sant&#xE9; mentale et soutien psychosocial (SMSPS) au profit des personnes d&#xE9;plac&#xE9;es internes et les communaut&#xE9;s h&#xF4;tes affect&#xE9;es dans les r&#xE9;gions du Centre-Nord, du Sahel et de l&#x2019;Est</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving health assistance to internally displaced persons and host communities in Oudalan and Yagha (Sahel region), Gourma and Tapoa (Est region) and Sanmatenga and Namentenga (Centre Nord region). This IOM project deploys mental health and psychosocial support teams and procures essential medicines. The project provides life-saving assistance to 15,500 people, including 6,100 women, 6,300 men, 3,100 children, and 1,550 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
